\section{Statement of the Problem}

In correlation to the goal of providing an alternative solution to digitally promote
the municipality of Tinambac's local tourism through a more interactive and entertaining
manner while providing the necessary information, the study aimed to address the
challenges of promoting local culture and tourism through gamification. Specifically,
it aimed to address the following questions:

\begin{enumerate}
  \item Which specific landmarks in the municipality of Tinambac will be incorporated
        into the gamified application?
  \item What design will the gamified application employ to provide information about
        landmarks in Tinambac?
  \item What design will the gamified application employ to provide the necessary
        entertainment on top of the essential information about the chosen specific
        landmarks?
  \item What is the level of acceptability of the gamified application in terms of:
    \begin{enumerate}
      \item Theme Implementation
      \item Game Element Functionality
      \item Game Mechanics
      \item Tourism Information Dissemination
    \end{enumerate}
\end{enumerate}

\section{Assumptions of the Study}

Based on the provided background of the study and subsequent problem statements, the
following assumptions were made:

\begin{enumerate}
  \item The study assumes that the key landmarks included in the gamified application
        will provide a good gamified touring experience.
  \item The study assumes that incorporating real-life settings in games can help in
        gaining the gamers' curiosity and make the player appreciate the contents of
        the game as well as the real-life counterparts that it was based on.
  \item The study assumes an immersive local setting approach in role-playing games
        (RPGs) will provide the necessary touch of entertainment and information needed
        to promote tourism in the municipality of Tinambac.
  \item The study assumes that the gamified application is acceptable in terms of theme
        implementation, game element functionality, game mechanics, and tourism
        information dissemination.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Scope and Delimitation}

The objective of this study is to provide an alternative approach to cultural
preservation and the promotion of local tourism to the set locale, the municipality of
Tinambac, throughout the school year 2025--2026. The study is focused on determining
the initial effect and result through the use of the gamified application, which will
be the main output of this study.

The study will focus on individuals aged 13 and above who have an interest in both
gaming and traveling, who want to know more about famous and important landmarks, and
who desire to know more about different places and their significance. The mapping of
the game will focus on the municipality of Tinambac, and only specific landmarks will
be involved; specifically, these landmarks will be limited to 4 specific areas within
the focus locale of this study. This is to ensure project completion in consideration
with the needed original assets to be gathered within the given timeframe. The game
will not include highly complex mechanics like advanced economic systems and political
structures. The development of the game as a capstone project shall be conducted within
the academic year 2025--2026.

This gamified application's content is set for 4 main parts; this is in consideration
of the aforementioned focus of only 4 specific landmarks. The gameplay will be good for
1--2 hours of playtime, and the content and the progression are set to a sequential
progression. The platforms will be, and may be limited to, the PC version of the game
with possible compatibility to kiosk-type setups. The game will not undergo major
updates and will be done and fully released. However, local testing and showcasing work
in progress will be done to ensure tracking of hitting milestones and displaying the
completion progress of the game to the game developers and testers.

\section{Significance of the Study}

Salubako, a gamified application for cultural preservation and local tourism, stands to
benefit the following:

\textbf{Local Tourism Office.} The study, especially the resulting output, will help in
promoting local tourism, greatly complementing the goal of the Department of Tourism of
Tinambac by showcasing local cultures and attractions that are rarely showcased to the
public, and the study supports destination advertisement by promoting lesser-known
attractions and encouraging more visits.

\textbf{Local Government Unit.} The results of this study will benefit the local
government unit of the municipality of Tinambac; the raw data or the consequent
interpretation of it will provide valuable insights to modernizing the locale's cultural
and tourism programs, which will help in transitioning to digital-first initiatives from
the current traditional methods.

\textbf{Gaming Industry.} The study provides tangible results; an apt example is the
gamified application that will add another entry to the gaming industry, especially
within the Bicol region, greatly showcasing the booming industry and the innovation
that comes with it.

\textbf{Other Researchers.} The study will help other researchers to utilize the
