\section{Definition of Terms}

\textbf{Salubako.} The term comes from the Bicol phrase ``Sa luba kong,'' which means
``in the midst of my''---The term is also inspired by the thoughts and lyrics of the
famous Bicol folk song titled ``Sarung Banggi.'' In this study, this term refers to the
name of the proposed game.

\textbf{Gamified Application.} Is the phrase that pertains to a software system that
incorporates game design elements and mechanics in a non-game context (such as education
or tourism) to improve user engagement and data retention. In the case of this study,
it refers to the resulting gamified application, Salubako, that incorporates specific
landmarks from the municipality of Tinambac for cultural preservation and promotion of
local tourism.

\textbf{Cultural Preservation.} The phrase refers to the systematic effort to protect,
maintain, and sustain both tangible and intangible cultural assets from decay, loss, or
forgetting. In this study, it applies to the digital reconstruction and use of specific
landmarks in the municipality of Tinambac.

\textbf{Gamification.} The term refers to the process of applying game elements to
other areas of activities, such as marketing or education. In the bounds of this study,
it refers to the similar concept, albeit applied for tourism purposes.

\textbf{Landmark.} In broad terms, it refers to a specific place or object that is
easily recognizable and signifies a specific location. In this study, it pertains to the
chosen specific locations within the municipality of Tinambac.

\textbf{Provincial Life.} It refers to the lifestyle, culture, and social dynamics
experienced in rural or less urbanized areas, often characterized by a slower pace of
life compared to urban areas. Within this study, this term refers to the way of life in
the Bicol Province.

