\subsection{System Architecture}

The system will consist of two major layers to its system architecture: the user
interface layer and the game logic layer. The user interface layer pertains to the main
menu, the setting menu, and the game screen itself. This layer targets the attention of
possible users as well as the level of retention for those who are already playing the
game. Looking back to the employed theoretical framework of this study, gamifying
something needs to provide visually appealing results that will work in tandem to garner
the feeling of an informative touring experience. On the side of the game logic layer,
it pertains to the inner workings of the system in context with the system architecture.
The technical components include the game engine, programming language, analytics tool,
and deployment environment. Ultimately, the two layers form the system architecture of
Project Salubako.

