\gdsection{Game Overview}

\indent Salubako is a game wherein you go around specific places in Tinambac, a municipality
in Camarines Sur, in which you travel from one place to another to familiarize yourself
with the sceneries, take photos, and interact with locals within those places.

\vspace{0.25em}
\noindent\textbf{Target Audience:}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Age 13 and up
  \item Players want to experience a glimpse of Bicol, specifically places in Tinambac
  \item Players who loves 2D top-down RPG game
\end{itemize}

\gdsection{Game Objectives}

\indent The objective of the game is to move around and explore the specific landmarks of
Tinambac-inspired settings to provide an alternative way of promoting local tourism in
a more interactive, entertaining, and informative manner.

\noindent\textbf{Progression:} The game progresses by traversing through various parts of
Tinambac to take photos of landmarks from the game's protagonist---Roberto. Each photo
you take corresponds to a puzzle level you need to solve. Solved puzzles unlock more
levels and progression throughout the game.

\noindent\textbf{Puzzles:} Players traverse through different parts of Tinambac to solve
various puzzles. Each puzzle corresponds to the picture of the real-life image. Solving
various puzzles allows you to unlock the next landmark as well as game rewards.

